						               													<description>The exclusive mini-expansion for participants of the Catan Big Game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If they pay 1 wool or 1 grain, players can send &amp;quot;settlers&amp;quot; to participate in the Big Game represented by a game table with slots for each of the ten production numbers. The first player to place three settlers on the table receives a bonus victory point that (similar to Greatest Army or Longest Road) has to be passed on if another player surpasses him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the Big Game table is full, new settlers may displace settlers already on the table - the production dice are rolled to determine where the new settler is placed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whenever the production number of a settler at the Big Game table is rolled, the player receives a laurel token. Laurel tokens can be exchanged for game benefits:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One laurel token will send the robber back to the desert.&amp;#10;Two laurel tokens let the player steal a card from the hand of another player.&amp;#10;Three laurel tokens let you choose a resource card from the bank.&amp;#10;Four laurel tokens let you build a road.&amp;#10;Five laurel tokens let you take a development card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
